    "summary": "I am a geneticist with a passion for plants. I have used quantitative and population genetic methods to study natural variation in plant photosynthesis, evolution of flower morphology, convergent adaptation to extreme environments, and cycto-nuclear interactions. My current focus is to use genetics and genomics to unleash the potential of wild species and orphan crops to create a more robust and sustainable agricultural system.\n\nAs a plant breeder I have experience with inbreeding and outbreeding crops, diploids and polyploids, dicots and monocots, fruits crops, grain crops, and tuber crops. I have also worked on well studied species i.e. wheat, tomato, peas and unknown wild species i.e. Lathyrus tuberosus",
